News Corp. CEO Said to Use London Visit to Support News Staff

-- B y   A m y   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-07-09T15:53:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-09/news-corp-ceo-said-to-use-london-visit-to-support-news-staff.html
News Corp. (NWSA)  Chief Executive Officer
 Rupert Murdoch  plans to use his visit to  London  to work with
News International staff as the company shuts down its News of
the World Sunday tabloid, said a person with knowledge of the
matter.  Murdoch, who heads to the U.K. this weekend for the News of
the World’s final issue, will work from News International’s
headquarters in Wapping, in the Docklands area of the U.K.
capital, said the person, who wasn’t authorized to speak
publicly.  Daisy Dunlop , a News International spokeswoman, declined to
comment.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Amy Thomson in London at 
 athomson6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
